==English==
===Etymology===
From ancient Greek [[διαλεκτική]] (''dialektike'') "the art of arguement through interactive questioning and answering", from [[διαλεκτικός]] (''dialektikos'') "competent debater".

===Noun===
'''dialectics'''
# plural of [[dialectic]]
# a [[systematic]] method of [[argument]] that attempts to [[resolve]] the [[contradiction]]s in [[opposing]] [[view]]s or [[idea]]s